Binary installation instructions:
 $ ./configure
 $ make install

Notable Runtime Dependencies:
 - gcc
 - perl
 - rsync
 - patch

For more information about Ksplice, please see <http://web.mit.edu/ksplice>.

If you want to build the software from source, you can do so by running:
 $ make distclean
 $ ./configure
 $ make
 $ make install

Notable Build Dependencies:
 - GNU binary file descriptor (BFD) library (tested against v2.15 through v2.18)
   (available in Debian's binutils-dev package and in other distributions)
